name: Economic Investment Trust Limited

In addition, $1,000,000 of 30-year 5% Collateral Trust Gold Bonds were issued in 1927, making the total amount of initial capital subscribed $2,612,500.  Economic is a closed-end investment corporation, the shares of which trade on the Toronto Stock Exchange under the symbol “EVT”. Economic is an investment vehicle for long-term growth through investments in common equities, as management believes that over long periods of time, common equities, as an asset class, will outperform fixed-income instruments or balanced funds. From time to time, however, assets of the Company may be invested in interest-bearing short-term securities pending the selection of suitable equity investments.

The project covers a significant deformation zone with highly anomalous Au-As signatures in historic rock, stream, and soil sampling. Ecstall: The 284 km2 district-scale Ecstall Project is located at tidewater and 60km from the booming resource town of Kitimat. The project covers the majority of the highly prospective and underexplored Ecstall Greenstone Belt. Thibert: The 124 km2 district-scale Thibert Project straddles the crustal-scale Thibert fault for 25km. The project covers a significant deformation zone with widespread silica-fuchsite alteration, common to orogenic systems. The company was founded by Dustin Perry and David Loretto on Septomber 07, 2017 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.

It focuses on the management of mineral properties in Northwest Manitoba and Northeast Saskatchewan. The company was founded on March 27, 1973 and is headquartered in Flin Flon, Canada.

name: Voyager Digital Ltd - Ordinary Shares - (Comm & Variable Voting)
description: Voyager Digital Ltd. engages in the provision of a fully functional suite of APIs and mobile apps to allow anyone who is legally able to do so the ability to trade, invest, earn and secure digital assets across multiple types of digital assets. The company was founded by Philip Eytan, Gaspard de Dreuzy, Stephen Ehrlich and Oscar Salazar on June 25, 1993 and is headquartered in New York, NY.

name: Valeo Pharma Inc.
description: Valeo Pharma, Inc. engages in the acquisitions, in-licensing or similar arrangements of patent protected, pharmaceutical products in specific therapeutic areas for the Canadian market. It focuses on injectable generic products. Its products include Onstryv, Synacthen,M-Eslon, Utrogestan, Ondansetron, and other hospital products. The company was founded by Steven Saviuk on March 27, 2003 and is headquartered in Kirkland, Canada.

name: Vitality Products
description: Vitality Products, Inc. engages in the manufacture, marketing, and distribution of natural health products, including vitamins, minerals, and nutritional supplements. Its products include Super Multi+, Time Release Super Multi+, Digest+, Relax+, Power Iron+Organic Spirulina, and Beauty Bundle-6. The company was founded in 1946 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.

name: Ventripoint Diagnostics Ltd
description: VentriPoint Diagnostics Ltd. is a medical device company, which engages in the development and commercialization of diagnostic tools that monitor patients with heart disease. Its Ventripoint Medical System produces critical heart information by processing standard information received from existing medical imaging equipment with its patented and proprietary methods incorporating Knowledge Based Reconstruction algorithms and proprietary cardiac databases. The company was founded by Joseph Ashley and Florence H. Sheehan on May 4, 2005 and is headquartered in Toronto, Canada.

name: VIQ Solutions Inc
description: VIQ Solutions, Inc. engages in the provision of artificial intelligence driven, digital voice, and video capture technology and transcription solutions. Its products include CapturePro, MobileMic Pro, NetScribe, and aiAssist. It operates through the Technology and Related Revenue, and Technology Services segments. The Technology and Related Revenue segment develops, distributes, and licenses computer-based digital solutions based on its proprietary technology. The Technology Services segment offers recording and transcription services. The firm serves the legal, criminal justice, insurance, government, corporate finance, and media industries. The company was founded on November 2004 and is headquartered in Mississauga, Canada.

name: Victory Resources Corporation
description: Victory Resources Corp. engages in the acquisition, exploration and development of mineral properties. It focuses on the drilling, mapping, sampling and planning for further development of its properties. The company was founded on February 8, 1984 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.

name: XR Immersive Tech Inc
description: XR Immersive Tech, Inc. is a VR/AR/MR technology company. It designs, programs, builds and installs self-contained and fully immersive escape room attractions including its flagship UNCONTAINED 6-player turn-key VR gaming solution. The company was founded on November 16, 2016 and is headquartered in Vancouver, BC.

name: Vanadiumcorp Resource Inc
description: VanadiumCorp Resource, Inc. is a mining and technology company, which engages in the acquisition and exploration of mineral properties in Canada. Its projects include Lac Doré Vanadium Project and Iron-T Vanadium Project in Quebec, Canada. The company was founded on October 23, 1980 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.

name: Vanguard FTSE Canadian Capped REIT Index ETF
description: Vanguard FTSE Canadian Capped REIT Index ETF seeks to track, to the extent reasonably possible and before fees and expenses, the performance of a broad Canadian real estate equity index that measures the investment return of publicly traded securities in the Canadian real estate sector.

name: Vanguard Retirement Income ETF Portfolio
description: VRIF is an actively-managed fund-of-funds that aims for consistent income and capital appreciation by investing in equity and fixed income securities globally.

name: Verano Holdings Corp
description: Verano Holdings Corp. engages in the provision of regulated cannabis products. Its products include Verano, Avexia, Encore, and MÜV. The company was founded on August 6, 2014 and is headquartered in Chicago, IL.

name: VR Resources Ltd
description: VR Resources Ltd. is a junior exploration company, which engages in the evaluation of mineral properties. Its properties include Hecla-Kilmer, Ranoke, Big Ten, Junction, New Boston, Reveille Silver, and Bonita. The company was founded on May 7, 2015 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.

name: VSBLTY Groupe Technologies Corp
description: VSBLTY Groupe Technologies Corp. is a software company. It engages in the business of commercializing various technologies relating to digital display platforms by combining interactive touch screens and data capture cameras, with cloud and edge based facial analytics. Its primary software modules include VisionCaptor, DataCaptor and Vector. The company was founded by Jay James Hutton and Fred Potok on August 1, 2018 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.

name: Vanguard S&P 500 Index ETF CAD-hedged
description: The investment objective of Vanguard S&P 500 Index ETF (the ETF) is to track, to the extent reasonably possible and before fees and expenses, the performance of the S&P 500 Index (the Index).

name: Vanstar Mining Resources Inc
description: Vanstar Mining Resources, Inc. engages in the acquisition, exploration, production, development and operation of mining properties. It focuses on the operation of Nelligan project. The company was founded on May 4, 2007 and is headquartered in Montreal, Canada.

name: Victory Square Technologies Inc
description: Victory Square Technologies, Inc. engages in the provision of online fantasy sports games. It operates through the following segments: Software, Investments, Gaming, Immersive Services, and Health. The company was founded on February 10, 2015 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.

name: Valdor Technology International Inc
description: Valdor Technology International, Inc. operates as an optical fiber components company specializing in the design, manufacture and sale of passive fiber optic components. The company is also involved in developing, manufacturing and marketing video streaming products. Its portfolio includes products like Streaming media products, Impact mount line products, Multiplexer products, and other related products. The firm focused on harsh environment products for the roll-out of fibre-to-the-home in North America with a splitter design. The company was founded on March 19, 1984 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.

name: Vertex Resource Group Ltd
description: Vertex Resource Group Ltd. provides environmental services. It serves clients in the oil and gas, oil sands, petrochemical, renewable energy, utilities, agriculture, forestry, mining, aggregate, and municipal sectors. The company also provides services to customers operating in industries such as energy, mining, utilities, private development, public infrastructure, construction, telecommunications, forestry, agriculture and government. The firm operates through the following business segments: Environmental Services and Environmental Consulting. The Environmental Services segment consists of a variety of services related to transportation; removal, storage disposal of materials; and maintenance of facilities. The Environmental Consulting segment consists of a variety of services related to assisting its clients to meet internal environmental standards, environmental legislation and related environmental compliance requirements. The company was founded in 1962 and is headquartered in Sherwood Park, Canada.

name: Virginia Energy Resources Inc
description: Virginia Energy Resources, Inc. is a development stage company, which engages in the exploration of uranium deposits. Its project includes the Coles Hill uranium deposit development located in Virginia. The company was founded on August 31, 2007 and headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.

name: Vulcan Minerals Inc

Its project portfolio includes Springdale Copper-Gold, Red Cross Lake Nickel, Gander Belt Newfoundland, and Red Moon Resources. The company was founded by Patrick J. Laracy on January 12, 1995 and is headquartered in St. John's, Canada.

description: VVC Exploration Corp. engages in the exploration and development of precious and base metals mineral properties. It operates through Canada and Mexico geographical segments. The firm's properties include Samalayuca, Cumeral, La Tuna, and Timmins. The company was founded on April 11, 1983 and is headquartered in Scarborough, Canada.

name: Vaxil Bio Ltd.
description: Vaxil Bio Ltd. is an immunotherapy biotech company. It is engaged in the development of immunotherapies such as neoantigen-like peptide products, and antibodies to treat cancer and infectious diseases. The firm's pipeline consists of ImMucin, SPmAb2, SPmAb6, and MTbuVax. The company was founded on July 26, 2006 and is headquartered in Toronto, Canada.

name: CI First Asset Morningstar International Value Index ETF

The company was founded by Jeff Hack and Jeff Young in 2000 and is headquartered in London, Canada.

name: VZLA- Vizsla Silver Corp Class A

It focuses on Panuco Silver-Gold Project located in the Panuco-Copala mining district in the municipality of Concordia in the State of Sinaloa, Mexico. The company was founded by Michael A. Konnert on September 26, 2017 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.

description: Champion Gaming Group, Inc. is a sports media, data and analytics company. It provides predictive and prescriptive analytical models, win probability applications and statistics in the sports industry for teams, media, fans and bettors. The company offers online sports wagering data, analytics and content to business and consumer customers through a subscription service model. Champion Gaming Group was founded by Kenneth Hershman and David Lubotta on February 2, 2021 and is headquartered in Toronto, Canada.

name: Western Alaska Minerals Corp
description: Western Alaska Minerals Corp. provides exploration services. It offers mines for gold, copper, and other minerals and 100% owned Illinois Creek Mining District. The company was founded on April 8, 2020 and is headquartered in Toronto, Canada.

name: Current Water Technologies Inc
description: Current Water Technologies, Inc. operates as an environmental water treatment company, which engages in development of environmental technologies. It also provides patented and proprietary technologies for the treatment of waste water and drinking water that are contaminated by metals or nutrients associated with the mining, metal processing, chemical, agricultural, municipal and waste management sectors. The company was founded by Gene S. Shelp and Barry J. Shelp on February 15, 1996 and is headquartered in Guelph, Canada.

name: Westbond Enterprises Corp
description: WestBond Enterprises Corp. engages in the provision of disposable paper and polyethylene business. Its product lines include clinical products such as examination table paper, sheets, pillowcases, hand towels, bathroom tissues, patient wipes, underlays for long term care facilities, air laid paper napkins, and gowns. The company was founded on October 18, 1989 and is headquartered in Delta, Canada.

name: WPD Pharmaceuticals Inc
description: WPD Pharmaceuticals, Inc. is biotechnology research and development company. The firm focuses on the research and development of medicinal products involving biological compounds and small molecules. Its products include WPD101, Berubicin, WP1066, WP1732, WPD102, WPD103, WP1220, and Annamycin. The company was founded on July 4, 2006 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.

name: Waterloo Brewing Ltd
description: Waterloo Brewing Ltd. engages in the production, sale, marketing and distribution of bottled, canned and draft premium beer under the Waterloo brand name and value beer under the Laker and Red Cap brand names. It also offers ready-to-drink alcoholic beverages under the Seagram trademark. The company was founded by James R. A. Brickman on February 20, 1984 and is headquartered in Kitchener, Canada.

description: Waste Connections, Inc. engages in the provision of non-hazardous waste collection, transfer, and disposal services. It offers its services to residential, commercial, landfill and transfer stations, and industries such as office, apartments multi-family, construction and demolition, property management, retail, restaurant, and manufacturing. It operates through the following geographical segments: Eastern, Southern, Western, Central, and Canada. The company was founded by Ronald J. Mittelstaedt on September 9, 1997 and is headquartered in Woodbridge, Canada.

Fagerheim on June 3, 2008 and is headquartered in Calgary, Canada.

It operates as a mineral resource company which focuses on copper asset development, and exploration and development of its two primary copper porphyry projects include Cristal and Escalones. The company is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.

name: Wedgemount Resources Corp
description: Wedgemount Resources Corp. engages in mining of natural resources. It focuses on acquiring, exploring and advancing exploration and evaluation assets in Canada. The company was founded on August 27, 2020 and is headquartered in Garibaldi Highlands, Canada.

It holds interest in the Eagle River Mine, Mishi Mine, Kiena complex, and Moss Lake Gold Mines properties. The company was founded on October 21, 1980 and is headquartered in Toronto, Canada.

description: Wondr Gaming Corp. builds partnerships and fosters community within the gaming and esports industries. Its business model unites brands and the global gaming community through loyalty & rewards, augmented reality, influencer advocacy, and tournament platform silos. The company was founded by Jonathan Dwyer and Michael Cotton and is headquartered in Toronto, Canada.

name: WeCommerce Holdings Ltd (Class A)

These businesses consist largely of Software as a Service, Digital Goods and Services businesses. The company was founded by Chris Sparling on March 4th, 2019 and is headquartered in Victoria, Canada.

name: Westaim Corp
description: The Westaim Corp. engages in the provision of long-term capital to businesses operating primarily within the global financial services industry. The firm invests, directly and indirectly, through acquisitions, joint ventures, and other arrangements. Its investments include Skyward Specialty and Arena. The Skyward Specialty segment is a U.S. based property & casualty diversified specialty insurance company group providing coverage primarily in the United States but also globally for certain risks. The Arena segment consists of two separate businesses, namely Arena Investors and Arena FINCOs. The Arena Investors including AI, an investment manager making fundamentals-based, asset-oriented credit investments on behalf of third-party investors; The Arena FINCOs, include specialty finance companies that primarily purchase fundamentals-based, asset oriented credit investments for their own account. The company was founded on May 7, 1996 and is headquartered in Toronto, Canada.

name: Wavefront Technology Solutions Inc

It specializes in design of fluid injection technology for oil well stimulations, secondary oil recovery, and environmental groundwater remediation. The company was founded by Brett C. Davidson, Timothy Spanos, and Maurice Dusseault in 1997 and is headquartered in Edmonton, Canada.

name: Canopy Growth Corporation
description: Canopy Growth Corp. engages in the production and sale of medical cannabis. The firm operates through the following segments: Global Cannabis and Other Consumer Products. The Global Cannabis segment encompasses the production, distribution and sale of a diverse range of cannabis and cannabinoid-based consumer products in Canada and internationally pursuant to applicable international and domestic legislation, regulations and permits. The Other Consumer Products segment encompasses the production, distribution and sale of consumer products by Storz & Bickel, This Works, BioSteel, and other ancillary revenue sources. It focuses on the treatment of chronic pain, seizures, muscle spasms, nausea, and loss of appetite. The company was founded by Bruce Linton on August 5, 2009 and is headquartered in Smith Falls, Canada.

name: Western Forest Products Inc.

It engages in the sale of lumber and logs, which includes timber harvesting, sawmilling logs into specialty lumber and value added lumber remanufacturing. Its products include outdoor living, home components, millwork, industrial, and non-residential. The company was founded in 1954 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.

It operates through the following segments: Clinical, Electronic Medical Records (EMR), Cybersecurity Services, Allied Health, Billing Services, Digital apps, and Corporate/Shared Services. The company was founded by Hamed Shahbazi on November 23, 2010 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.

It develops evidence-based formulations and protocols that empower patients to overcome neurological, psychological and mental health ailments caused by trauma. The company was founded by Daniel Carcillo, Dawn McCollough, and Chad Bronstein and is headquartered in Homer Glen, IL.

name: West Mining Corp
description: West Mining Corp. operates as a mineral exploration company, which focuses on the acquisition and exploration of advanced and prospective early-stage projects. Its projects include Kena and Daylight, Spanish Mountain, Junker, and Blue Cove. The company was founded on August 28, 2017 and is headquartered in Vancouver, CA.

name: Wall Financial Corp.

It operates through the following segments: Rental, Hotel, Development, and Corporate. The Rental segment involves in the ownership and management of revenue producing residential and commercial properties. The Hotel segment deals with the ownership and management of hotel properties. The Development segment relates to the development and sale of residential housing units. The company was founded on January 31, 1969 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.

name: West Fraser Timber Co., Ltd.
description: West Fraser Timber Co. Ltd. is a diversified wood products company, which engages in producing lumber, engineered wood products (oriented strand board, laminated veneer lumber, medium density fiberboard, plywood, and particleboard), pulp, newsprint, wood chips, other residuals and renewable energy. Its products are used in home construction, repair and remodeling, industrial applications, papers, tissue, and box materials. The firm operates through the following segments: Lumber, North America Engineered Wood Products, Pulp & Paper, Europe Engineered Wood Products, and Corporate. The company was founded by Henry Holman Ketcham Jr, Samuel Kendall Ketcham, and William Peters Ketcham on January 28, 1955 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.

name: Westward Gold Inc
description: Westward Gold, Inc. is a mineral exploration and development company. It is engaged in the acquisition and exploration of the mineral resource properties. The firm holds interest in the Mulloy and Toiyabe Gold projects. The company was founded on April 19, 2017 and is headquartered in Toronto, Canada.

The Knapdale Property is an early exploration stage project prospective for orogenic quartzgold-silver lodes that comprises three contiguous sub-properties (Stronchullin prospect; Ormsary North and Ormsary South). The Lagalochan Property is considered a copper-gold porphyry prospect for future exploration. The company was founded by David Harry Williamson Dobson on December 5, 2016 and is headquartered in Scotland, the United Kingdom.

name: White Gold Corp
description: White Gold Corp. engages in the acquisition and exploration of mineral properties. Its projects include Sixty Mile, Klondike, White-Stewart, Coffee Trend East, and West and Beaver Creek. The company was founded on March 26, 1987 and is headquartered in Toronto, Canada.

name: Whitehorse Gold Corp

The company was founded by Gareth Oswald Thomas on April 17, 1998 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.

It focuses on developing its intermediate-advanced stage exploration Record Ridge South Magnesium Property located in British Columbia. The company was founded by Frank Marasco, Jr. on August 29, 2003 and is headquartered in Calgary, Canada.

description: The Western Investment Company of Canada Ltd. is a private equity company, which engages in the acquisition of ownership positions in successful Western Canadian companies. It operates through the following segments: GlassMasters, Golden Health Care, Ocean Sales, and Foothills. The GlassMasters segment provides mobile repair and installation units. The Golden Health Care segment offers full-service retirement homes. The Ocean Sales segment imports and sells retail products through unique marketing channels across North America. The Foothills segment produces and distributes butter and ice cream products. The company was founded by Scott A. Tannas on October 28, 2015 and is headquartered in High River, Canada.

description: West Island Brands, Inc. engages in the development of marijuana for medical purposes. It focuses on the acquisition, evaluation, and disposing of exploration properties and also to evaluate opportunities to invest in parties that are applicants under the Health Canada Access to Cannabis for Medical Purposes Regulation. The company was founded on November 13, 2007 and is headquartered in Toronto, Canada.

It focuses in pursuing oil and gas properties in international locations including the Middle East and Africa. The company was founded on August 15, 2007 and is headquartered in Calgary, Canada.

name: WildBrain Ltd
description: WildBrain Ltd. engages in the production and distribution of content, television, and consumer products representation. It operates through the following segments: Content Business, Television, and Consumer Products Represented. The Consumer Products Represented segment includes representation of internal and third-party brands. The Content Business segment includes production and distribution of content business, including its own production of its own proprietary content, third-party production service work, distribution of proprietary, and third party content and licensing royalties from its owned IP and brands. The Televsion segments deals with television broadcasting. The company was founded by Charles William Bishop, Steven Graham DeNure, and Michael Patrick Donovan on February 12, 2004 and is headquartered in Halifax, Canada.

The firm's operating segment include acquisition, exploration, and development of mineral properties for economically recoverable reserves in Canada and providing services using the Computer Aided Resources Detection System. The company was founded on February 23, 1996 and is headquartered in Brossard, Canada.

It offers an 'all-in-one' suite that provides companies with marketing, promotion, lead generation, and sales conversion capabilities. The company provides proprietary cloud-based software for lead generation, marketing automation, and analytics, including landing pages, social promotions, website pop-ups, online forms, lead activity tracking, and email marketing. Wishpond Technologies founded in 2009 by Ali Tajskandar and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.

name: Wajax Corp
description: Wajax Corp. engages in providing industrial products and services. The firm operates an integrated distribution system, providing sales, parts and services to customers in diverse sectors of the Canadian economy, including construction, forestry, mining, industrial and commercial, oil sands, transportation, metal processing, government and utilities, and oil and gas. Its brands include Hitachi, Hyster, MTU, Allison Transmission, Eaton and SKF. The company was founded by Bernard Joseph Coghlin in 1858 and is headquartered in Mississauga, Canada.

name: Well Told Company Inc (The)

description: Willow Biosciences, Inc. is a biotechnology company. It develops synthetic biology solutions for opioid biosynthesis. The firm offers biosynthetic production systems for plant-derived active pharmaceutical ingredients (API) and intermediates. The company operates through the following segments: Research and Development, Analytical Testing, and Corporate. Willow Biosciences was founded on April 15, 1981 and is headquartered in Calgary, Canada.

The firm focuses on using aeroponics technology in its cultivation process. The company was founded by Earl Connors on February 6, 2018 and is headquartered in Calgary, Canada.

Its project portfolio includes Denison property, Parking Offset properties, East Range properties, Fenelon, and Beschefer. The company was founded on March 24, 1966 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.

It holds interest in Atacama Salar, Ollague, Valsequillo, Coronado and Kootenay projects. The company was founded by Hendrik van Alphen on October 7, 1994 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.

name: Walmart CDR (CAD Hedged)
description: Walmart, Inc. engages in retail and wholesale business. The Company offers an assortment of merchandise and services at everyday low prices. It operates through the following business segments: Walmart U.S., Walmart International, and Sam's Club. The Walmart U.S. segment operates as a merchandiser of consumer products, operating under the Walmart, Wal-Mart, and Walmart Neighborhood Market brands, as well as walmart.com and other eCommerce brands. The Walmart International segment manages supercenters, supermarkets, hypermarkets, warehouse clubs, and cash and carry outside of the United States. The Sam's Club segment comprises membership-only warehouse clubs and samsclubs.com. The company was founded by Samuel Moore Walton and James Lawrence Walton in 1945 and is headquartered in Bentonville, AR.

name: George Weston Ltd.

It operates through the following segments: Loblaw, Choice Properties, and Weston Foods. The Loblaw segment stands for Loblaw Companies Ltd., which engages in the retail of food and drugs and provision of financial services. The Choice Properties segment pertains to Choice Properties Real Estate Investment Trust. The Weston foods segment produces baked goods. The company was founded by George Weston in 1882 and is headquartered in Toronto, Canada.

name: WonderFi Technologies Inc.
description: Wonderfi Technologies, Inc. operates as a financial technology company, which engages in the development of a technology platform to facilitate investments in the emerging industry of decentralized finance. The company was founded by Ben Samaroo, Cong Ly and Dean Sutton on November 1, 1990 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.

name: BMO Women in Leadership Fund ETF
description: This funds objective is to increase the value of  your investment over the long term by investing  primarily in issuers that promote a gender diverse  leadership environment.

The firm operates through the Animation Production segment and Networks and Platforms segment. The Animation Production segment offers animation services on a work-for-hire basis as well as financing and producing its own intellectual property for licensing and distribution. The Networks and Platforms segment operates an animation multi-channel network on the YouTube platform. The company was founded by Robert Ezrin in 1991 and is headquartered in Toronto, Canada.

description: Winpak Ltd. engages in the manufacture and distribution of packaging materials and related packaging machines. The firm operates through following segments: Rigid Packaging & Flexible Lidding; Flexible Packaging; and Packaging Machinery. The Rigid Packaging & Flexible Lidding segment includes the rigid containers and lidding product groups. The Flexible Packaging segment includes the modified atmosphere packaging, specialty films and biaxially oriented nylon product groups. The Packaging Machinery segment includes horizontal fill and seal machines for preformed containers and vertical form, fill and seal pouch machines for pumpable liquid and semi-liquid products and certain dry products. The company was founded on September 29, 1975 and is headquartered in Winnipeg, Canada.

name: Wheaton Precious Metals Corporation

It focuses on the following precious metals streams: Salobo, Penasquito, Antamina, Constancia, Stillwater, San Dimas, Sudhury, Zinkgruvan, Yauliyacu, Neves-Corvo, Pascua-Lama, Rosemont, Voisey's Bay, and others. name: Westport Fuel Systems Inc.
description: Westport Fuel Systems, Inc. is a transportation technology company. It engages in the engineering, manufacture, and supply of alternative fuel systems and components. The firm operates through the following segments: Transportation, The Cummins Westport, Inc. (CWI) Joint Venture, and Corporate. The Transportation segment designs, manufactures, and sells alternative fuel systems and components for transportation applications. The CWI Joint Venture segment serves the medium and heavy-duty on highway engine markets. The Corporate segment refers to the public company activities, corporate oversight, and general administrative duties. The company was founded on March 20, 1995 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.

Bowers on March 18, 1996 and is headquartered in Calgary, Canada.

name: Western Copper & Gold Corp
description: Western Copper & Gold Corp. is an exploration stage company, which focuses on the development of Casino Project. The company was founded on March 18, 2006 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.

name: Western Resources Corp
